SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PROFESSIONAL LICENSE FEES RAISED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Professionals and tradespeople working in Hermosa Beach, such as contractors, 
doctors and lawyers, will pay a higher fee when they renew their annual 
business licenses this year. 
</P>
<P>
Increases in the flat fees -- now $150, plus $12 for each of the professional's 
employees, in most categories -- will be tied to annual rises in the cost of 
living. 
</P>
<P>
Retail businesses, which pay fees based on a percentage of gross income, will 
not be affected by the new measure, which voters approved in November. The City 
Council adopted a policy resolution Tuesday to increase the fees. 
