<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 5 TREATED AFTER FUMES FORCE STORE EVACUATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Five people were treated at a hospital Thursday after vapors from a spilled 
load of pesticides forced the evacuation of a Thousand Oaks discount store, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The five, all store employees, were treated at Westlake Community Hospital and 
released after they inhaled fumes from 15 broken containers of the pesticide 
malathion, said Ventura County Fire Department spokeswoman Cece Grives. The 
containers were in five boxes accidentally dropped in a storeroom at a K mart 
store in the 300 block of Hampshire Road, Grives said. 
</P>
<P>
No other injuries were reported in the 11:14 a.m. accident, which forced the 
evacuation of 100 customers and 75 employees, Grives said. It was unknown why 
the boxes fell, she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
