<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL TRACK; 
</P>
<P>
HARROLD GIVES CANYON SHARE OF LEAGUE TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Canyon Coach Dave DeLong calls Corey Harrold the heart and soul of the Canyon 
High boys' track team and on Thursday, Harrold powered the Cowboys to a 71-56 
victory over Palmdale in a Golden League meet at Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
Harrold, a senior, won the 200 meters in 22.8 seconds, the 400 in 49.8 and the 
triple jump with a leap of 41 feet, 3 1/2 inches. 
</P>
<P>
The Canyon victory guaranteed the Cowboys (5-1 overall, 4-0 in league meets) a 
share of the league title. They can clinch the title outright with a win over 
Saugus next Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Other Canyon winners included sophomore Dave Hartman in the 3,200 (9 minutes, 
55 seconds), Clint Beauer in the 110-meter high hurdles (16.1) and Jamil Austin 
in the high jump (6-2). 
</P>
<P>
In other boys' meets: 
</P>
<P>
Royal 103, Newbury Park 33 -- Sophomore Tim Ross won three events for Royal in 
the Marmonte League meet at Newbury Park. 
</P>
<P>
Ross took the high jump -- his specialty -- at 6-2, the long jump at 20-10 and 
the triple jump at 42-6 1/2 as the Highlanders (3-1) kept pace with Thousand 
Oaks in the Marmonte League race. 
</P>
<P>
Dean Hansen added victories in the shotput (48-1 1/2) and discus (144-2) for 
Royal. 
</P>
<P>
Sean Wolpin won the 120-yard high hurdles (15.1) and the 330-yard intermediate 
hurdles (42.3) for Newbury Park (2-2). 
</P>
<P>
Rio Mesa 89, Camarillo 47 -- Patrick Van Scoy and Lester Smith led the Spartans 
to victory in the nonleague meet at Rio Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
Van Scoy won the shotput (53-3) and the discus (160-6) and Smith, a senior, won 
the long jump (20-9) and the triple jump (45-3). 
</P>
<P>
Jeff Garner won the high jump with a personal best of 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
Juniors Abe Valdez and Chad Malesich led Camarillo as Valdez won the 1,600 in 
4:29.1 and the 3,200 in 9:31.7, and Malesich took the 800 in 1:59.3 
</P>
<P>
Alemany 71, St. Francis 56 -- Tony Borquez won three events to lead Alemany 
(3-2, 1-2) in the Del Rey League meet at St. Francis. 
</P>
<P>
Borquez, eighth in the 400 at last year's state championships, won the 100 
yards in 10.1, the 220 in 22.8, the 440 in 52.2, and anchored Alemany's 440 
relay win (45.0). 
</P>
<P>
Carpinteria 77, Oak Park 59 -- Coley Candaele won the 440 and the 880 to lead 
visiting Carpinteria in a Tri-Valley League match. 
</P>
<P>
Candaele ran the 440 in 50.0 and the 880 in 2:03.3. Candaele also anchored 
Carpinteria (2-1, 1-1) to victory in the mile relay in 3:31.5. 
</P>
<P>
For Oak Park (2-1, 1-1), Jason Stein won the 100-yard dash in 10.3 and the 
330-yard intermediate hurdles in 42.4. Jess Garner won the 110 high hurdles in 
15.3. 
</P>
<P>
Agoura 90, Santa Ynez 46 -- The Chargers captured 10 individual events to win 
the Frontier League meet at Agoura. 
</P>
<P>
Bryan Dameworth, the two-time defending state Division I cross-country 
champion, won the 800 meters (2:00.7), 1,600 meters (4:27.7) and 3,200 meters 
(10:00.6). Teammate Jeff Ingalls won the 100-meter dash (11.2), 400 meters 
(51.2) and anchored the Chargers (3-2, 3-0) to victory in the 1,600 meter relay 
(3:35.7). 
</P>
<P>
In girls' meets: 
</P>
<P>
Rio Mesa 90, Camarillo 36 -- Shannon Wiebelhaus won three events and Angela 
Burnham won two as the Spartans remained undefeated (6-0) in the nonleague meet 
at Rio Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
Wiebelhaus won the 200 (26.0), 300-meter low hurdles (47.1), triple jump 
(32-11) and ran the second led on Rio Mesa's victorious 400 relay (50.5). 
</P>
<P>
Burnham won the 100 in 12.1, the 400 in 57.4, anchored the 400 relay (50.5) and 
ran the first leg on the 1,600 relay (4:19.5). 
</P>
