<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTS ET CETERA: SDSU SIGNS TWO TO PLAY BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two community college players, Steve McClellan and Marty Dow, have signed 
national letters of intent to play basketball at San Diego State University. 
</P>
<P>
McClellan, a 6-foot-6, 235-pound forward from Arizona Western, averaged 12.6 
points and 10.2 rebounds and helped the Matadors win the Arizona state 
community college championship. 
</P>
<P>
Dow, a 7-0 center from Northeast Oklahoma A&amp;M, averaged 10.1 points and 7.3 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Stefan Mumaw, a 6-9 center from Irvine University High, signed with Christian 
Heritage. 
</P>
<P>
Dawn Wood, a pitcher from Castle Park High, signed to play softball at Arizona 
State. Wood tied a national record last season by throwing consecutive perfect 
games for the Trojans. 
</P>
<P>
BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State (25-16) lost its second consecutive game to host New Orleans, 
5-1. Jeff Barry scored the Aztecs' only run, when he doubled, stole third and 
came home on an errant throw from the Privateers' catcher. 
</P>
<P>
Southern California College scored three runs with one out in the bottom of the 
ninth to defeat visiting UC San Diego, 7-6. Dave Ligerman went three for four. 
Jim Martinez went two for two with two RBIs and Gary Fessia was two for four 
with two RBIs for the Tritons (17-13). 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
The University of San Diego won at No. 2 through No. 6 singles and defeated No. 
19 Long Beach State, 5-1, at USD's west courts. Chris Toomey, Mark Farren, J.R. 
Farren, Dan Mattera and Curtis Dadian won for No. 15 USD (22-6). The 49ers fell 
to 14-10. 
</P>
