<P>
MORNING REPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press.FROM JAPAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four Japanese organizations have contributed $1.4 million to underwrite six 
one-hour PBS programs on "Nature Perfected." The series, due on PBS in the fall 
of 1990, "will explore the old world and the new, shed light and information on 
a variety of cultures, and examine how gardens have epitomized humanity's place 
in the natural and universal order." The contributors: Seibu Saison Group, 
Sumitomo Bank Ltd., Suntory Corp. and the Japan Assn. for the International 
Garden and Greenery Exposition. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
