<P>
KHOMEINI'S EX-HEIR REPORTED IN CUSTODY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ATHENS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Ayatollah Hussein Ali Montazeri, who was once in line to succeed the 
Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini as Iran's supreme leader, is under house arrest in 
the holy city of Qom, a source in Tehran said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Word of Montazeri's status came by telephone shortly after a Baghdad-based 
Iranian opposition group said Revolutionary Guards and security men had 
arrested relatives of Montazeri after his fall from grace. 
</P>
