<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLF ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
STEWART AND PERRY SHARE LEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Payne Stewart shot a bogey-free, six-under-par 65 Thursday for a share of the 
first-round lead in the $800,000 Heritage golf tournament at Hilton Head 
Island, S.C. 
</P>
<P>
Stewart was tied with Kenny Perry, who got his share of the lead with a 12-foot 
birdie putt on the 18th hole. Stewart and Perry are two strokes ahead of Bob 
Eastwood and Rocco Mediate. 
</P>
<P>
Nick Faldo of England, in his first round since winning the Masters, shot a 68 
with only 23 putts. 
</P>
<P>
That, however, was five more than the record-matching 18 putts needed by Kenny 
Knox in a round of 69. Knox chipped in three times and had 12 one-putt greens 
as he tied the PGA Tour record for fewest putts in a round. 
</P>
<P>
Gene Littler shot a six-under-par 66 for a one-shot lead in the first round of 
The Tradition, a new $600,000 tournament on the Senior PGA Tour at Scottsdale, 
Ariz. 
</P>
</TEXT>
