<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 2 CHILDREN DIE AFTER FALLING INTO POOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A toddler and his 3-year-old sister died Thursday after they fell into the 
rooftop swimming pool of a Westlake apartment building when they were left 
unsupervised for a few minutes, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Deiongh, 1 1/2, was pronounced dead at Childrens Hospital, where his 
sister, Christine, died several hours later. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles Police Sgt. Sam Layton called the drownings accidental. He said the 
children's mother, Song Deiongh, had taken them to a recreation area atop the 
seven-story building west of downtown and left them alone while she used a 
nearby restroom. When she returned, the children were at the bottom of the 
seven-foot-deep pool. 
</P>
</TEXT>
