<P>
Trading Cola for Ships: Norwegian ship brokers have cooked up a deal in which 
Soviet shipyards may build up to 85 new vessels worth nearly $2.6 billion that 
will be partly paid for in Pepsi, pizza and fried chicken. Ole-Jacob Libaek, 
who helped broker the deal, said the U.S. soft-drink giant Pepsi-Cola Co. wants 
