it exports annually to the Soviet Union. Libaek said, "Pepsi Cola is very big 
in the Soviet Union and the Russians also want Pizza Huts and Kentucky Fried 
Chicken," both owned by Pepsi. The Soviets "prefer to trade goods for goods 
because of their deficit of foreign currency," he said. 
