<P>
MORNING REPORT: KUDOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and international 
news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A group of UCLA law students awarded actors James Woods ("True Believers") and 
Jimmy Smits ("L.A. Law") with plaques Wednesday night honoring them for 
"showing the legal profession in a positive light." Both actors received the 
awards from the UCLA Entertainment Law Society for playing idealistic 
attorneys, determined to right wrongs and ensure justice for disadvantaged 
clients. "This is a special kudo that even Oscar can't match," said Woods. 
</P>
