<TEXT>
<P>
National Public Radio's "All Things Considered" will broadcast a special 
feature today to note the 50th anniversary of John Steinbeck's Pulitzer 
Prize-winning novel, "The Grapes of Wrath." Actor Peter Coyote will read 
selections from the novel, interspersed with interviews with farm workers in 
Oklahoma and California whose stories parallel those in the book. "All Things" 
airs 3:30-5:30 p.m. KPCC-FM (89.3), 4-7 p.m. KCRW-FM (89.9). ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
