<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: THE ARTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mayor Tom Bradley recommended an additional $1.9 million for grants to cultural 
organizations in his fiscal 1989-1990 city budget proposal Thursday. The 
recommendation jibes with interim spending plans for the proposed $20 million 
Los Angeles Endowment for the Arts, the city's new cultural funding program, to 
become fully operational in July, 1990. If the City Council approves Bradley's 
proposal, which contains $450,000 for a new citywide arts festival project and 
an additional $155,000 for the city's mural program, $3 million in grants will 
be awarded in July. Bradley's action shows "a great effort to upgrade city 
support for the arts immediately," said Cultural Affairs Department General 
Manager Al Nodal. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
