</P>
<P>
SERVITE'S DEREK BROWN TO SKIP ALL-STAR GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Servite High School running back Derek Brown, who set the Orange County 
single-season rushing record with 2,301 yards last season, has decided not to 
play in the Orange County All-Star football game, according to North Coach John 
Barnes. 
</P>
<P>
"We called all the players or their coaches to find out who wanted to play in 
the game and the Servite athletic director said that Derek would not being 
playing," Barnes said. "He didn't give any reason. I guess Derek just didn't 
want to play. 
</P>
<P>
Brown broke former Edison star Kerwin Bell's mark of 2,226 yards set in 1979. 
Brown also scored 30 touchdowns, including kickoff returns of 92 and 93 yards 
in the Southern Section Division I playoffs. He could not be reached. 
</P>
<P>
The full team is scheduled to be announced Saturday. 
</P>
