<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIFE; 
</P>
<P>
NICKLAUS, WATSON TO PLAY BRITONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ST. MELLION, England 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Americans Jack Nicklaus and Tom Watson will meet the last two U.S. Masters 
champions, Britons Sandy Lyle and Nick Faldo, in a transatlantic challenge golf 
tournament this summer. 
</P>
<P>
Organizers said today that the better-ball match would take place at St. 
Mellion Golf Club in Cornwall July 16, just before the start of the British 
Open. The four players met in a similar made-for-television match at St. 
Mellion last year when torrential rains hit the course. 
</P>
<P>
No details on prize money were available. 
</P>
</TEXT>
